This refers to **Fordism**, where Henry Ford introduced the **assembly line and job specialization** in 1913, drastically increasing productivity and allowing workers to earn higher wages (e.g., $5/day, a significant sum at the time). This enabled them to afford the cars they produced, creating a mass market. The system relied on repetitive, specialized tasks to boost efficiency and output.
